[{"short_id":"sbe8ln","created_at":"2026-05-23T17:01:32.000-05:00","title":"remind(1) -- calendar and alarm program","url":"https://dianne.skoll.ca/projects/remind/","score":1,"flags":0,"comment_count":0,"description":"\u003cp\u003e\"Remind is a sophisticated calendar and alarm program designed to run on Linux and other UNIX-like\nsystems.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n","description_plain":"\"Remind is a sophisticated calendar and alarm program designed to run on Linux and other UNIX-like\r\nsystems.\"","submitter_user":"netzego","user_is_author":false,"tags":["linux","unix"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/sbe8ln","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/sbe8ln/remind_1_calendar_alarm_program"},{"short_id":"oyzqgz","created_at":"2026-05-23T17:01:32.000-05:00","title":"It's time to talk about my writerdeck","url":"https://veronicaexplains.net/my-first-writerdeck/","score":1,"flags":0,"comment_count":0,"description":"","description_plain":"","submitter_user":"facundoolano","user_is_author":false,"tags":["linux","vim"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/oyzqgz","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/oyzqgz/it_s_time_talk_about_my_writerdeck"},{"short_id":"umbcno","created_at":"2026-05-23T16:46:23.000-05:00","title":"Software engineering at the tipping point - YouTube","url":"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=2n41YjR5QfU","score":1,"flags":0,"comment_count":0,"description":"","description_plain":"","submitter_user":"dunyakirkali","user_is_author":false,"tags":["practices","video"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/umbcno","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/umbcno/software_engineering_at_tipping_point"},{"short_id":"kz0m2n","created_at":"2026-05-23T16:44:43.000-05:00","title":"“Long-Term Support” doesn’t mean what you think","url":"https://pointieststick.com/2026/05/23/long-term-support-doesnt-mean-what-you-think/","score":1,"flags":0,"comment_count":0,"description":"","description_plain":"","submitter_user":"Aks","user_is_author":false,"tags":["linux"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/kz0m2n","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/kz0m2n/long_term_support_doesn_t_mean_what_you"},{"short_id":"5ob3rh","created_at":"2026-05-23T16:28:40.000-05:00","title":".NET (OK, C#) finally gets union types","url":"https://andrewlock.net/exploring-the-dotnet-11-preview-2-dotnet-gets-union-types/","score":3,"flags":0,"comment_count":0,"description":"","description_plain":"","submitter_user":"ubernostrum","user_is_author":false,"tags":["dotnet"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/5ob3rh","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/5ob3rh/net_ok_c_finally_gets_union_types"},{"short_id":"fmdyt7","created_at":"2026-05-23T15:38:20.000-05:00","title":"The Architecture of BerkeleyDB","url":"https://aosabook.org/en/v1/bdb.html","score":3,"flags":0,"comment_count":1,"description":"","description_plain":"","submitter_user":"typesanitizer","user_is_author":false,"tags":["databases"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/fmdyt7","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/fmdyt7/architecture_berkeleydb"},{"short_id":"yfpl8d","created_at":"2026-05-23T15:11:14.000-05:00","title":"Procedural Fascicle for R7RS Large Scheme","url":"https://r7rs.org/large/fascicles/proc/","score":3,"flags":0,"comment_count":0,"description":"\u003cp\u003eScheme Working Group 2 is pleased to announce the first draft of the\nsecond part of the R7RS-Large Foundations, the \u003cstrong\u003e\"Procedural\nFascicle\u003c/strong\u003e.\"  This draft encompasses the familiar block programming forms, such as \u003ccode\u003elambda\u003c/code\u003e, \u003ccode\u003elet\u003c/code\u003e, \u003ccode\u003eif\u003c/code\u003e, \u003ccode\u003eor\u003c/code\u003e, and \u003ccode\u003eset!\u003c/code\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe draft is available here:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://r7rs.org/large/fascicles/proc/\" rel=\"ugc\"\u003ehttps://r7rs.org/large/fascicles/proc/\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe biggest new feature is the ability to mix definitions and expressions in bodies, such as the body of a \u003ccode\u003elambda\u003c/code\u003e.  For example, the following is now valid:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cpre lang=\"scheme\"\u003e\u003ccode\u003e(define (map f lst)\r\n  (unless (list? lst)\r\n    (error 'map \"not a list\" lst))\r\n  (define (map* lst acc)\r\n    (if (null? lst)\r\n        (reverse acc)\r\n        (map* (cdr lst) (cons (f (car lst)) acc))))\r\n  (map* lst '()))\r\n\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eWe welcome any and all comments on the draft.  Anyone can comment by:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eFiling an issue on the \u003ca href=\"https://codeberg.org/scheme/r7rs\" rel=\"ugc\"\u003eR7RS-Large issue tracker\u003c/a\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eSending mail to the \u003ca href=\"https://groups.google.com/g/scheme-reports-wg2\" rel=\"ugc\"\u003eWorking Group 2 mailing list\u003c/a\u003e (you do not need a Google account)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eSending mail to the \u003ca href=\"https://scheme-reports.simplelists.com/\" rel=\"ugc\"\u003eScheme Reports mailing list\u003c/a\u003e at \u003ca href=\"mailto:scheme-reports@scheme-reports.org\" rel=\"ugc\"\u003escheme-reports@scheme-reports.org\u003c/a\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eSending mail to the corresponding member Peter McGoron at \u003ca href=\"mailto:code@mcgoron.com\" rel=\"ugc\"\u003ecode@mcgoron.com\u003c/a\u003e.  He will forward your comment to the public issue tracker.  Please indicate if you wish to be anonymous.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n","description_plain":"Scheme Working Group 2 is pleased to announce the first draft of the\r\nsecond part of the R7RS-Large Foundations, the **\"Procedural\r\nFascicle**.\"  This draft encompasses the familiar block programming forms, such as `lambda`, `let`, `if`, `or`, and `set!`.\r\n\r\nThe draft is available here:\r\n\r\n\u003chttps://r7rs.org/large/fascicles/proc/\u003e\r\n\r\nThe biggest new feature is the ability to mix definitions and expressions in bodies, such as the body of a `lambda`.  For example, the following is now valid:\r\n\r\n```scheme\r\n(define (map f lst)\r\n  (unless (list? lst)\r\n    (error 'map \"not a list\" lst))\r\n  (define (map* lst acc)\r\n    (if (null? lst)\r\n        (reverse acc)\r\n        (map* (cdr lst) (cons (f (car lst)) acc))))\r\n  (map* lst '()))\r\n```\r\n\r\nWe welcome any and all comments on the draft.  Anyone can comment by:\r\n\r\n- Filing an issue on the [R7RS-Large issue tracker](https://codeberg.org/scheme/r7rs)\r\n- Sending mail to the [Working Group 2 mailing list](https://groups.google.com/g/scheme-reports-wg2) (you do not need a Google account)\r\n- Sending mail to the [Scheme Reports mailing list](https://scheme-reports.simplelists.com/) at \u003cscheme-reports@scheme-reports.org\u003e\r\n- Sending mail to the corresponding member Peter McGoron at \u003ccode@mcgoron.com\u003e.  He will forward your comment to the public issue tracker.  Please indicate if you wish to be anonymous.","submitter_user":"aag","user_is_author":false,"tags":["lisp"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/yfpl8d","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/yfpl8d/procedural_fascicle_for_r7rs_large"},{"short_id":"8dnsat","created_at":"2026-05-23T14:11:33.000-05:00","title":"Reverse engineering circuitry in a Spacelab computer from 1980","url":"http://www.righto.com/2026/05/reverse-engineering-spacelab-computer.html","score":2,"flags":0,"comment_count":0,"description":"","description_plain":"","submitter_user":"calvin","user_is_author":false,"tags":["hardware","historical","reversing"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/8dnsat","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/8dnsat/reverse_engineering_circuitry_spacelab"},{"short_id":"dqig3h","created_at":"2026-05-23T13:57:06.000-05:00","title":"On the \u003cdl\u003e","url":"https://benmyers.dev/blog/on-the-dl/","score":11,"flags":0,"comment_count":0,"description":"","description_plain":"","submitter_user":"runxiyu","user_is_author":false,"tags":["a11y","web"],"short_id_url":"https